    (Extracted from R documentation) ARIMA: Will fit the best ARIMA (Autoregressive integrated moving average) model according to either AIC, AICc or BIC value. * ARIMA_FORCE_SEASONALITY: Same as ARIMA but forcing seasonality THETA: Theta method is equivalent to simple exponential smoothing with drift ETS: Exponential smoothing state space model ETSDAMPED: ETS forcing a damped trend (either additive or multiplicative) BAGGEDETS: Bergmeir et al (2016) for bagging ETS forecasts STL: Forecasting by Seasonal Decomposition of Time Series by Loess NN: Neural Network Time Series Forecasts HYBRID: Forecasting by Hybrid Models PROPHET: Prophet Forecaster by Facebook
